		<title>08EMPLOYMENT</title>
		<content>  Three generations ago most people    
 walked to work (29% men and 67%       
 working wives). 25% men used the      
 train, 4% men had cars, while 12.5%   
 travelled by horse. The rest lived at 
 their place of work.                  
  One generation later the car was the 
 most common form of transport for men 
 and working wives. A smaller number of
 men travelled by train.               
  Now the majority of parents travel by
 car whatever the distance.            
  Only 0.5% men and 3% women use the   
 bus to get to work.                   
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
